org.jppf.utils.pooling

Class AbstractBoundedObjectPoolQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jppf.utils.pooling.AbstractObjectPoolQueue<T>
      • org.jppf.utils.pooling.AbstractBoundedObjectPoolQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the elements in the pool.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ObjectPool<T>

    public abstract class AbstractBoundedObjectPoolQueue<T>
extends AbstractObjectPoolQueue<T>
    An extension of AbstractObjectPoolQueue which specifies a maximum size for the pool.

    In this implementation, objects are still created dynamically if the pool is empty, however the put(T) method does not return an element to the backing queue if the pool size >= max size.

    the AbstractBoundedObjectPoolQueue.size() method is also overriden to provide results in constant time insteat of O(n) in the super class, since it is used frequently when comparing current pool size with the max size.
